on a romantic getaway.

296
00:13:13,869 --> 00:13:16,670
How do I know
what you said?

297
00:13:16,672 --> 00:13:19,739
Damn you and your
noise-cancelling breasts.

298
00:13:22,611 --> 00:13:23,743
Hello.

299
00:13:23,745 --> 00:13:25,445
Hi.
Hey, buddy.

300
00:13:25,447 --> 00:13:27,547
You excited for Texas?

301
00:13:27,549 --> 00:13:29,883
Oh, very much so.

302
00:13:29,885 --> 00:13:32,953
It's not every day you get to
tour NASA with a real astronaut.

303
00:13:32,955 --> 00:13:36,089
Who's the real astronaut?

304
00:13:37,558 --> 00:13:39,659
Buzz Aldrin.

305
00:13:39,661 --> 00:13:42,095
Oh. Yay!

306
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,909
Howard?

307
00:13:55,911 --> 00:13:57,944
Howard?

308
00:13:57,946 --> 00:14:00,146
Howard?

309
00:14:01,849 --> 00:14:03,817
What now?

310
00:14:03,819 --> 00:14:06,119
I have to go
to the bathroom.

311
00:14:06,121 --> 00:14:07,654
You just went
to the bathroom.

312
00:14:07,656 --> 00:14:10,357
I didn't use it because
it didn't seem safe.

313
00:14:10,359 --> 00:14:14,461
Despite all my e-mails, the
toilet didn't have a seatbelt.

314
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:17,764
Well, it still doesn't.

315
00:14:17,766 --> 00:14:19,299
I realize that,

316
00:14:19,301 --> 00:14:22,969
but safety concerns went out
the window two apple juices ago.

317
00:14:22,971 --> 00:14:25,071
Fine.

318
00:14:26,307 --> 00:14:28,441
Why are you
getting annoyed?

319
00:14:28,443 --> 00:14:31,011
I'm trying to be
a better friend,

320
00:14:31,013 --> 00:14:34,581
but you constantly say
and do irritating things.

321
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:36,683
Like when?
When?!

322
00:14:36,685 --> 00:14:37,984
How about in the car?

323
00:14:37,986 --> 00:14:40,320
I'm an astronaut,
and you know it.

324
00:14:40,322 --> 00:14:43,356
You just don't like admitting
it, because you're jealous.

325
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:48,561
Well, truth be told,

326
00:14:48,563 --> 00:14:51,164
as a child, I did dream
of going to space.

327
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:53,133
Those astronauts
were my heroes.

328
00:14:53,135 --> 00:14:55,268
And...

329
00:14:55,270 --> 00:14:58,471
when you got to go,
it was hard for me.

330
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:01,341
Thank you.

331
00:15:01,343 --> 00:15:03,443
Because it made me
realize they'll just

332
00:15:03,445 --> 00:15:05,645
send anyone up there.

333
00:15:06,948 --> 00:15:08,949
Aren't you going
to let me out?

334
00:15:08,951 --> 00:15:09,459
No.

335
00:15:09,484 --> 00:15:11,385
But I still need
to use the bathroom.

336
00:15:11,386 --> 00:15:14,654
Here you go. Be creative.

337
00:15:17,392 --> 00:15:20,126
What's the matter?
Scared of a little turbulence?

338
00:15:20,128 --> 00:15:23,430
No, turbulence is
just the equalization

339
00:15:23,432 --> 00:15:25,532
of diurnal temperature
variations in the atmosphere.

340
00:15:25,534 --> 00:15:27,334
I'm not scared at all.

341
00:15:28,704 --> 00:15:30,937
Oh, apple juice,
stay where you are.

342
00:15:31,772 --> 00:15:33,373
Oh, this is nothing.

343
00:15:33,375 --> 00:15:35,041
I experienced way worse

344
00:15:35,043 --> 00:15:37,043
when I was plummeting
back to Earth,

345
00:15:37,045 --> 00:15:39,579
